&lt;p&gt;As shown in our &lt;a href="get-started.md"&gt;Get Started&lt;/a&gt; guide, Oakestra uses 3-4 building blocks to operate.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Orchestration</title><link>/version/0.4.301/docs/oakestra/orchestrators/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/version/0.4.301/docs/oakestra/orchestrators/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;#APIs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Root Orchestrator APIs &lt;a href="https://app.swaggerhub.com/apis-docs/giobarty/oakestra-root_api/v1#/"&gt;OpenApi Spec&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Task Scheduling</title><link>/version/0.4.301/docs/oakestra/scheduling/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/version/0.4.301/docs/oakestra/scheduling/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="how-does-the-scheduling-work-in-oakestra"&gt;How does the scheduling work in Oakestra?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oakestra&amp;rsquo;s architecture is composed of two tiers. Resources are divided into clusters. A cluster is seen as the aggregation of all its resources. A job is first scheduled to a cluster, and then the cluster scheduler decides the target worker.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>